President Biden has declared a major disaster for the Soboba Band of Luiseño Indians due to a severe winter storm and flooding that occurred from February 23 to February 26, 2023. This declaration allows federal aid to supplement the Tribal Nation's efforts in the affected areas. The Soboba Band of Luiseño Indians and certain nonprofit organizations can receive federal funding for emergency work, facility repairs or replacements, and hazard mitigation measures on a cost-sharing basis. Benigno Bern Ruiz of the Federal Emergency Management Agency has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.